social_posts.post_text: A season to forget but a year to remember. Grateful to still have the opportunity to do what I love and not be forced into something different after this year. Really thankful for my friends and family for helping me through this summer. Looking forward to making the most of the opportunities that I have in front of me and getting back on the race track🤙

Saying goodbye to the @yeticycles squad after 3 years, man time flies. Endlessly thankful for all the support and amazing opportunities over the years. It was fun travelling the world and making memories with this crew. Thank you all 💙

New year and hopefully a new me? 
Excited for what’s next

2023 with @the_yt_mob 👊
Fresh off a team camp with the new crew! 
Stoked to get this season going ✈️ full team vid link in bio.

Crashed about a month ago and destroyed my spleen. Somehow they managed to save it after a couple procedures. Pretty gutted/frustrated and with the front loaded schedule this year it looks like I’ll be missing the majority of the season. Going to be taking this time to get back to a 100% as I was still working my way back to that after last summer’s incidents. Thank you to the @the_yt_mob for the continued support.

Good day out riding my @yt_industries Szepter yesterday. Still a ways away from riding the MTB but things are going in the right direction. 
My golf game on the other hand 😵‍💫 
📸 @evan_wall
Solid week of training with @fit4racing. UK weather never disappoints. Getting closer to being back on the bike and couldn’t be more excited for it!
Quick vacation to 🇬🇷 to end this Euro trip. Excited to ride my @yt_industries Capra now😁.

Bikes are great😎. Taking it slow to get comfortable again. 4 months felt like forever! Big thanks to the people helping me get back on my feet.

First race in 14 months yesterday! It’s been a long road to get back to this point. I didn’t make it very far with a double flat on top of the world but nice to be out there and feel some race day nerves again. Off to big sky this week for some more racing! #ytmob #ytcapra #liveuncaged
Slip n’ Slidin out here today! Another mess of a day tomorrow. 🫡 @bigmountainenduro

Great weekend in big sky for my first complete race in well over a year. 2nd place with a few stage wins feels great to feel some speed again! 
@caspervangeest keeping the bike running perfect as per usual👌.

First @uci_mtbworldseries enduro finish in almost two years. 
Finished P22 in the end! 
Had a pretty clean day. Just a little slide out on stage 1. Feels so good to get that race feeling back. Started to find some speed on the last two stages with a p12 and p14🤙. Stoked to build on this for the next one in a couple weeks. Cheers team for a great first race👊.

11th place for me in Chatel to finish off my mini World Cup season. Stoked to get a 3rd and 4th place on stage 5 and 7 showing myself that I can still mix it up at the front. Feels like I’m just starting to catch some momentum so stoked to keep it going into the off season! Big thanks to everyone in my corner helping me get back to this point. It’s been a hell of a ride and stoked to start putting that behind me and moving on to bigger and better things🤙 #liveuncaged

Good weekend out at the @usopenmtb 🤙. 🥉 place in the enduro for me. Going home healthy and hungry for more after my first successful block of races in a couple years. 

Big thanks to the @the_yt_mob for all the support this year through the good and bad. Next season couldn’t come soon enough! #liveuncaged #ytcapra
